            <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Subsidy control</h1>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Provision of this Voucher Token is a subsidy to your business and is provided as a Small Amount of Financial Assistance under Article 364.4 of the Trade and Cooperation Agreement.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                It is the responsibility of the business to ensure that acceptance of this Voucher Token will not cause it to exceed the maximum permitted threshold for Small Amounts of Financial Assistance  or <a href="https://www.economy-ni.gov.uk/articles/de-minimis-aid" target="_blank" class="govuk-link"> De Minimis aid</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                For further information, please refer to the [<a href="/termsandconditions/terms" class="govuk-link">terms and conditions</a>].
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Subject to exchange rate fluctuations, you are able to receive a total of approximately <strong>£330,000</strong> in Small Amounts of Financial Assistance (taking into account De Minimis aid received before 1 January 2021) over a period of three fiscal years.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Where you are a goods or wholesale electricity company with operations based in Northern Ireland, or your business is otherwise in scope of the State aid provisions in the Northern Ireland Protocol, the Voucher Tokens are provided as De Minimis aid.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                You are able to receive a total of <strong>200,000 Euros</strong> in De Minimis aid over a period of three fiscal years.
            </p>
